        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 10:14PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 1014 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles south of Pritchett, or 19 miles southwest of Springfield,
moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Springfield, Walsh, Pritchett, Vilas, Campo, and Stonington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM MDT for
southeastern Colorado.</instruction>
